[{'number': 1, 'created': '2016-06-10 23:05:34.000000000', 'files': ['neutron/agent/l2/extensions/trunk.py', 'setup.cfg'], 'message': '[WIP] Basic trunk L2 agent extension for the OVS agent

Currently this patch is only for illustration purposes.

When Nova/os-vif creates the 1st patch port pair from a trunk bridge to
br-int, this L2 agent extension is triggered and creates the patch port
pairs necessary for the trunk's subports. When Nova/os-vif deletes the
1st patch port pair, this L2 agent extension is triggered to remove the
trunk's subport patch pairs.

When creating the patch port pairs for the subports, the extension is
not responsible for adding the local vlan tag on the br-int patch ports
(and other required port config). This is handled by the core of the OVS
agent when it detects that new ports have been added to br-int. The
ports that correspond to subports must be bound in order for the OVS
agent to complete the OVS port config on br-int. Otherwise, the OVS
agent will consider these subport patch ports to be "dead" and won't
complete their configuration.

Partially-implements: blueprint vlan-aware-vms
Change-Id: I7fc61eb7fa0c2cc6d9312a40f98532c30c06fd92
'}]
commit_message:
[WIP] Basic trunk L2 agent extension for the OVS agent

Currently this patch is only for illustration purposes.

When Nova/os-vif creates the 1st patch port pair from a trunk bridge to
br-int, this L2 agent extension is triggered and creates the patch port
pairs necessary for the trunk's subports. When Nova/os-vif deletes the
1st patch port pair, this L2 agent extension is triggered to remove the
trunk's subport patch pairs.

When creating the patch port pairs for the subports, the extension is
not responsible for adding the local vlan tag on the br-int patch ports
(and other required port config). This is handled by the core of the OVS
agent when it detects that new ports have been added to br-int. The
ports that correspond to subports must be bound in order for the OVS
agent to complete the OVS port config on br-int. Otherwise, the OVS
agent will consider these subport patch ports to be "dead" and won't
complete their configuration.

Partially-implements: blueprint vlan-aware-vms
Change-Id: I7fc61eb7fa0c2cc6d9312a40f98532c30c06fd92

commit_message:
Introduce Elements for Log Aggregation

This commit introduces the 'overcloud-logging' element,
which installs the necessary packages for the log aggregation
in the overcloud.

Additionally, it updates the 'puppet-modules' element to include
the puppet modules required for deploying log aggregation components
in the overcloud (puppet-fluentd)

Change-Id: Ib739de0ca70b8f85c0b4fb3c9ea57fd9c2b0fa61

shared pools and in that way influence the resulting list of resources
we fetch to compare with shared=False list later.

commit_message:
Support LLDP data as part of interfaces in inventory

To support multi-tenant networking in Ironic we need to be able to
discover not just the NICs a baremetal machine has but also the physical
connectivity to switches in the network.

This patch collects LLDP (Link Layer Discovery Protocol) data as part of
the list interfaces stage of the generic hardware manager. This
information can then be processed by the ironic inspector to populate
the local link information on each ironic port.

The processing done on this data in ironic python agent is limited, this
is to allow for server side processing hooks to process as much or as
little of the data as they want. This is to allow for multi-vendor
environments that might use different parts of the LLDP packet to use a
generic ramdisk and configure the processing server side using inspector
plugins.

Reserved fields switch_port_descr and switch_chassis_descr have been
deprecated for removal in Ocata in favor of passing the whole packet.

Change-Id: Idae9b1ede1797029da1bd521501b121957ca1f1a
Partial-Bug: #1526403

commit_message:
Adding ability to set 'properties' via Glance

The 'Glance' plugin lacked the ability to set properties
on the images that were created via the plugin.  This patch
adds that ability.  This also includes the change made in
commit 7d059fdc00278acd3859b25a39caf1e3741bb51d, which
made the image_properties argument optional.

Change-Id: If2c73050ed8335b3a22b79bb7ce28189de046427

commit_message:
Fix calls to assert_not_called() and assert_called_once()

There is no assert_not_called() and assert_called_once()
method in mock, as described here:
https://code.google.com/p/mock/issues/detail?id=159
Fix these calls to use assertFalse() and
assert_called_once_with() attribute instead.

Closes-Bug: #1316167
Change-Id: I0e09702167ad21b3eba08d121b323abe1005fba9

commit_message:
Cleanup Liberty to Mitaka upgrade corner cases not necessary anymore

This corner case was handled to consider the version of non reporting
agents which could have the qos extension enabled.

It's not necessary anymore and has been therefore removed.

The devref details have been updated to present tense, as they should be.

Change-Id: Ie40d3f34a46950f5124cf8ef7f486d90513271f4

commit_message:
Dump functest server logs into gate output

If we could see the server side log at gerrit gate (in particular,
the case gate failed), it will be worthful to know what's happen
(be wrong) in the implementation.

This patch attempt to dump swift/ansible/storlets log into the log
dir in test directory only when that is called via tox. Hopefully,
someone else can work to set up each testing process to log indivisual
files in test dir though.

Change-Id: I1dd03edd4fd1fcd18a3b297d6789d52b2d22dc38

The gateway ip can be configured to be different than the seed ip.
If this is done however, there is no port configured as the gateway
which results in a non-functioning configuration. Someone may want
to move the gateway away from the seed to provide the ability to
shutdown the seed but continue to access the remainder of the cloud
environment.  If the gateway ip is different from the seed ip, a port
is created on brbm and assigned the gateway ip.

Change-Id: If35210827c3568d5c47fbae10db2b99083f0d3ab
Closes-Bug: 1337475
'}]
commit_message:
Provide support for different gateway and seed ips

The gateway ip can be configured to be different than the seed ip.
If this is done however, there is no port configured as the gateway
which results in a non-functioning configuration. Someone may want
to move the gateway away from the seed to provide the ability to
shutdown the seed but continue to access the remainder of the cloud
environment.  If the gateway ip is different from the seed ip, a port
is created on brbm and assigned the gateway ip.

Change-Id: If35210827c3568d5c47fbae10db2b99083f0d3ab
Closes-Bug: 1337475

commit_message:
WADL to RST migration (part 2)

This brings the Images API Reference to the glance tree as part of
the effort described here:
https://wiki.openstack.org/wiki/Documentation/Migrate#API_Reference_Plan

This patch contains the content of the Images v2 API reference converted
to RST.  The content has been corrected where I noticed divergences with
reality.

The tox environment to build the api-ref docs is introduced in the
dependency.

Note to reviewers: The conversion project is ongoing, that is, the doc
team is continuing to develop tools (for example, to display the
response codes in a table) and converging on a style for these docs.
So this isn't a final product, there will be more patches later.  While
this patch is not perfect, it is pareto-optimal with respect to content
(it's at least as good as the current guide, and better in at least one
place).  Thus my advice, should you choose to take it, is that we should
merge this patch to get these docs in-tree, and make improvements as
additional patches rather than try to get everything perfect on this
patch.

Change-Id: Iacfc38d048fbaa0d48f5831977793bc84cc30700
Depends-On: I51dfaf1832108466f115ab183838c5f28e138312

commit_message:
Only load timestamp service plugin in timestamp tests

Do not allow the timestamp plugin tests to load all of the default
service plugins to prevent possible resources from being leaked
from those plugins.

commit_message:
Make auto allocate plugin safe for unit/func tests

The registry.subscribe calls cannot happen at import time because
a module is imported only once for a test runner, but the callback
manager is wiped out for each test.

This changes the subscribe calls to happen on object construction
instead of at import time.

Change-Id: I1f0cc65000ea613dda58dea3a1a85621c26cda9a
Closes-Bug: #1567855
(cherry picked from commit a56bbac059f7fe434a8b92370f1363a17e700e74)

commit_message:
Fix argument order for assertEqual to (expected, observed)

assertEqual expects that the arguments provided to it should be
(expected, observed). If a particluar order is kept as a convention,
then it helps to provide a cleaner message to the developer if Unit
Tests fail. The following patch fixes this issue.

Change-Id: I85628a1d60fa809f80d658ed7d66dbd5d7e03010
Closes-Bug: #1259292

commit_message:
Add undercloud config wizard UI

This is a simple PyQt4 UI that can be used to generate a sane
config from only three inputs, rather than the more numerous ones
exposed in undercloud.conf.  It also does a certain amount of
validation of the options if they are customized after generation.

Change-Id: Idb71db16af24e326228b5a3661b4c9be9985e3b7

commit_message:
Translate properties before update

This adds the translation rule call to properties before update, so that
we can remove resource code that refers to deprecated properties. The
new ones are used everywhere with the expectation that the translation
occurred.

Change-Id: Ibdf91ae711f82de5c60896f2452e2872bb3dc9cb
Closes-Bug: #1518676

subject: Do not prompt for scope options with default scoped tokens
revisions:
[{'number': 2, 'created': '2016-06-15 19:00:13.000000000', 'files': ['openstackclient/api/auth.py', 'openstackclient/shell.py', 'openstackclient/common/clientmanager.py'], 'message': 'Do not prompt for scope options with default scoped tokens

This changes the scope validation to occur after a token has already
been created.

Previous flow:

1. Validate authentication options.
2. Validate authorization options if the command requires a scope.
3. Create a token (using authentication + authorization options)
4. Run command.

This means that scope was being checked, even if a default scope was
applied in step 3 by Keystone.

New flow:

1. Validate authentication options.
2. Create token (using authentication + authorization options)
3  Validate authorization options if the command requires a scope and
   the token is not scoped.
4. Run command.

Change-Id: Idae368a11249f425b14b891fc68b4176e2b3e981
Closes-Bug: 1592062
(cherry picked from commit a8ee5db6711e0015bfa0bd45f1fc17412c34f580)
'}]
commit_message:
Do not prompt for scope options with default scoped tokens

This changes the scope validation to occur after a token has already
been created.

Previous flow:

1. Validate authentication options.
2. Validate authorization options if the command requires a scope.
3. Create a token (using authentication + authorization options)
4. Run command.

This means that scope was being checked, even if a default scope was
applied in step 3 by Keystone.

New flow:

1. Validate authentication options.
2. Create token (using authentication + authorization options)
3  Validate authorization options if the command requires a scope and
   the token is not scoped.
4. Run command.

Change-Id: Idae368a11249f425b14b891fc68b4176e2b3e981
Closes-Bug: 1592062
(cherry picked from commit a8ee5db6711e0015bfa0bd45f1fc17412c34f580)

commit_message:
Do not prompt for scope options with default scoped tokens

This changes the scope validation to occur after a token has already
been created.

Previous flow:

1. Validate authentication options.
2. Validate authorization options if the command requires a scope.
3. Create a token (using authentication + authorization options)
4. Run command.

This means that scope was being checked, even if a default scope was
applied in step 3 by Keystone.

New flow:

1. Validate authentication options.
2. Create token (using authentication + authorization options)
3  Validate authorization options if the command requires a scope and
   the token is not scoped.
4. Run command.

Change-Id: Idae368a11249f425b14b891fc68b4176e2b3e981
Closes-Bug: 1592062
(cherry picked from commit a8ee5db6711e0015bfa0bd45f1fc17412c34f580)

Add helper function to iterate over parameters

The helpers.iterate_parameters function allows to iterate over lines of
INI-like files along with a context of information, such section,
parameter and value.

commit_message:
Reset default_domain_id before the keystone task

The default_domain_id should be removed from keystone.conf after restore
of DB and before to apply the keystone puppet task to avoid of using the
configured domain as a default.

Change-Id: I05a6c48532e8042496b3d8ccef53d65bf8c44653

commit_message:
libvirt: virtlogd: introduce domain xml element "log"

The new domain XML elements <log> can be attached as sub-element to
character devices. This change only introduces the domain XML config
object. A following change will make that part of character devices.
Another following change will use this object to store the
boot messages of an instance when the parent char device uses the
"virtlogd" as backend for its stdout/stderr output.

blueprint libvirt-virtlogd
Depends-On: I9a1fbf005b0f48df90093a346579d9ddc64f7846

Change-Id: I72b7a301697bc551a66c966573fee392341730af

commit_message:
libvirt: virtlogd: refactoring 4 before functional change

The logic to create the char devices of a guest is now extracted into
single pieces with single responsibilities. The refactoring is now good
enough to use the "virtlogd" feature with a following change.

blueprint libvirt-virtlogd

Change-Id: I3046f1682f47a1a7d9bf613a603da71179077e44

commit_message:
libvirt: virtlogd: refactoring 3 before functional change

The logic to create the char devices for a guest has a lot of conditionals
which makes it hard to understand.
This change inverts some of these to reduce the nested levels of IFs. The
flow is then easier to understand and the functional changes for the
"virtlogd" feature in a following change will be easier to review.

blueprint libvirt-virtlogd

Change-Id: Iabe9810b77e2bfe1529e68a1c8c3d75a3425c29e

[{'number': 6, 'created': '2016-06-20 16:07:35.000000000', 'files': ['nova/virt/libvirt/driver.py', 'nova/tests/unit/virt/libvirt/test_driver.py'], 'message': 'libvirt: virtlogd: refactoring 2 before functional change

The conditional logic to create the char devices is spread over 2 methods
which makes it confusing to understand under which conditions which char
devices get created for the guest. As the "virtlogd" feature will append a
sub element "log" to the first(!) char device in a following change, a
refactoring of these conditionals will make the future change easier to
understand.
This change:
* inlines method "_create_serial_console_devices"
* changes the unit tests accordingly

This refactoring step makes it later easier to understand which functional
changes get introduced and under which conditions.

blueprint libvirt-virtlogd

commit_message:
libvirt: virtlogd: refactoring 2 before functional change

The conditional logic to create the char devices is spread over 2 methods
which makes it confusing to understand under which conditions which char
devices get created for the guest. As the "virtlogd" feature will append a
sub element "log" to the first(!) char device in a following change, a
refactoring of these conditionals will make the future change easier to
understand.
This change:
* inlines method "_create_serial_console_devices"
* changes the unit tests accordingly

This refactoring step makes it later easier to understand which functional
changes get introduced and under which conditions.

blueprint libvirt-virtlogd

Change-Id: I06c12a58049737ef49f5cf366499a928f2f6e95f

commit_message:
libvirt: virtlogd: refactoring 1 before functional change

The methods "_create_consoles" and "_create_serial_console_devices" have
many conditional cases and return or append devices. It's confusing to
read and understand them.
This change:
* moves all console related things to "_create_consoles"
* renames "_create_consoles"
* adds docstrings to understand which objects are used

This refactoring step makes it later easier to understand which functional
changes get introduced and under which conditions.

blueprint libvirt-virtlogd

Change-Id: Ibd764f0bc6236bd53a920a5fbf805119bdb4ff78

commit_message:
Add update_file context manager for local files

The subprocess.update_file function provides an ability to update
content of a local file by iterating over lines of an original file and
forming a result content in a temporary file to replace the original
file in the end. This function is very useful to change configuration
files.

Change-Id: I433a5da67887b231400dd63131799019f45c277c

commit_message:
configurable port option for l2gw agent

whenever l2gw agent IP:PORT is configured in manager table
of ovsdb server, it has to be configured in l2gateway_agent.ini
so that l2gw agent can listen for the connection request from ovsdb
server for the configured port.

Change-Id: Iac81c41cbac7daf43e72c12f094d6fefe33ce749
Closes-Bug: 1580869
(cherry picked from commit 4cb660909f0224aa65cc17f36c3c12dcde609770)

commit_message:
check the interface type in the request

check for interface type while creating l2-gateway.
it should be list of dict.if not raise an appropriate message.

for ex: request body for l2-gateway-create is as below.
{"l2_gateway": {"name": "gw2", "devices": [{"interfaces": [{"name": "i1"}]}, "device_name": "switch2"}]}'

Change-Id: I65430efa1a3ed4416e649f0377d9dff7fafc5b57
Closes-Bug: 1548361
(cherry picked from commit 1639819a20fb2227551508df5b0aef6e0d0c59e0)

commit_message:
[Tempest] HotFix for broken CI jobs

Recently merged commit to "neutron-fwaas" project [1] started using
one of Tempest's modules that appeared after version our plugin uses.
So, implement hotfix-workaround until we make all compatibility changes
to latest Tempest in our plugin.

For the moment, we cannot switch to latest Tempest as we already
have incompatibility for it, see bug [2].

[1] https://review.openstack.org/#/c/326150/
[2] https://bugs.launchpad.net/manila/+bug/1586129

Change-Id: I44655c83cc5588c5b94d0fad81162dd0c238b5b4
Closes-Bug: #1589964
(cherry picked from commit e96e7cb299ee5d057f86f5e68b26ecc2d425c938)

commit_message:
[Tempest] Stop using deprecated Tempest opts

Currently, Manila CI Tempest jobs use deprecated options of Tempest.
Recently, latest version of Tempest dropped them [1].
Manila CI jobs work ok, because they check out specific version of
Tempest. But it will work until first Devstack update for some one
more Tempest feature and then we will be forced to use latest Tempest
again. Switch to supported approach of setting up users in Tempest,
to avoid such sudden blockers.

[1] I8c24cd17f643083dde71ab2bd2a38417c54aeccb

Squashed with [Tempest] Bump tempest version
Fix small incompatibility that left to be done and bump Tempest version
to unblock our CI jobs.
(cherry picked from commit e2aecad5476908c8a6d40dfa0298e92ca3872f76)

Change-Id: I5b3ebab52ea1401f6f7a116d1260268eb10ebe0c
Closes-Bug: #1586129
(cherry picked from commit 82a571c4861c03512f234d7e1f536900568a9afa)

commit_message:
Remove requirements job from Rally

Rally team is willing to maintain requirments.
There are 2 major reasons:
- We would like to have fixed versions for each version of rally
  and we are cutting releases each 3 weeks
- We would like to use fixed versions in gates so new versions of
  libs won't block our gates and we will have time to test new
  versions before they are changed

P.S. We are going to keep our requirements compatible with OpenStack libs

Change-Id: Ie08bb538e09b0247ce6948f235d05c9c1d118cd1

commit_message:
improve tests for mask_password and mask_dict_password

All the tests used a very 'strong' password of mypassword and it
wasn't apparent in reviewing some new tests whether the masking was
being done of the 'word' password in mypassword or the command option
or dictionary key.

So I've taken the liberty to rewrite all the tests with a better
password.

commit_message:
Documentation face-lift

Changing the doc structure plus adding a step by step s2aio installation
instructions, as well as deployment installation instructions

Bonuses:
1. Allowing an empty docker repo prefix (no preceding ip:port)
2. Installation scripts to use openstack cli instead of keystone cli
3. Changing the /opt/ibm prefix to /opt/storlets in the Docker container
4. Simplified deployment installation scripts: moving all mgmt tools
aside for future refactoring
5. storlets-swift-install repo moved from OpenI-Beam to eranr for
   maintainability reasons

Change-Id: Id40b0984bc8325f0d2a2977b4c266adb2e95b997

commit_message:
Fix CI and add nodepool-xenial.yml file

To run Beaker jobs in OpenStack Infra, we need this file so we run tests
on the right nodeset

Beaker jobs are broken because of specinfra 2.59.1

commit_message:
Heat upstream default policy.json works in devstack

It does not however work in TripleO, and the ping test is failing
with master Heat because of this. I tried submitting a revert[1] in
Heat, but they have functional tests, so it is not broken...

The only option left is using puppet-heat to override the broken
default.

[1] https://review.openstack.org/#/c/332206/

Change-Id: I2c674a2e01eeacd17d3158f378be2d6ceeedc309

commit_message:
Revert "use utf8 as default charset for all tables in mysql db"

Reverting change id I15a864dd1ad18aa1b3e3ff7fe511405d62a119cc.
We can't modify old migrations, since they might already have been
run some places, and you'll end up with different database structures
depending on which version you ran.

The correct fix for this problem is to add a new migration that fixes
the structure.

Change-Id: Ifd3f4f4f062bab386cc89f490c37ac9f25abdcdb

to log at a particular level, with the default set to
'notice'.

haproxy is configured to log to /var/log/haproxy/haproxy.log
which is a symlink to the same path on /mnt/state. Note that
this patch changes the default rsyslog.d/haproxy.conf to use

Change-Id: I9dd33ddfa337055c65b4d67a1c70690590dd5b1e

commit_message:
Configure haproxy logging

haproxy is currently not logging. This change adds support
to log at a particular level, with the default set to
'notice'.

haproxy is configured to log to /var/log/haproxy/haproxy.log
which is a symlink to the same path on /mnt/state. Note that
this patch changes the default rsyslog.d/haproxy.conf to use
a haproxy log dir instead of logging directly to /var/log.

Change-Id: I9dd33ddfa337055c65b4d67a1c70690590dd5b1e

Rules are not persistent unless they are added with add-rule.
Change add rule to accept -t parameter to specify a table
other than filter and change nova element to use add-rule
for a rule it is adding to the nat table. Create this rule

Change-Id: Ic54102f78cfa107b06dec20886a2e0ce8f078148

commit_message:
Nova rule needs to be added with add-rule for persistence

Rules are not persistent unless they are added with add-rule.
Change add rule to accept -t parameter to specify a table
other than filter and change nova element to use add-rule
for a rule it is adding to the nat table. Create this rule
earlier in the configure sequence so that neutron rules are
not loaded when it is added.

Change-Id: Ic54102f78cfa107b06dec20886a2e0ce8f078148

commit_message:
Ceilometer Service Update/Upgrade in TripleO

Support for an update/upgrade strategy that allows Ceilometer to
minimize the amount of data loss.

The event producing services are stopped (if running) and the queue
is drained and all the data in transit is stored to the database
from the collector agent.

When the collector has consumed all the data in the queue it is
restarted and subsequently all the event producing and querying
services are started.

Change-Id: I598d8ed6a92c8b4892d54f815dd664451d4c63f2

commit_message:
Install pkg-config to use ceilometer-agent-compute

Using ceilometer-agent-compute element causes DIB to fail during image
creation with the following error:

Exception: pkg-config binary is required to compile libvirt-python

Installing pkg-config package addresses this issue, hence pushing this
as a install.d command before trying to install libvirt-python.

Closes-Bug: #1350684
Change-Id: I6dbe588d4ac86c42403e4ec3bab589d326121029

subject: configure keystone with apache
revisions:
[{'number': 5, 'created': '2014-05-05 20:35:35.000000000', 'files': ['elements/keystone/files/keystone.conf', 'elements/keystone/os-refresh-config/post-configure.d/70-keystone', 'elements/keystone/install.d/keystone-source-install/70-keystone'], 'message': "configure keystone with apache

Allow configuration of keystone with Apache via environement variable.
Below are the reasons why we need Apache:

1.  Keystone federation support requires Apache. Federation can only be
supported in conjunction with Apache as it needs both mod_mellon and mod_shib.

2. Performance. Unlike Nova or Swift, Keystone is using eventlet with a
single thread instead of multiple worker processes. So can't take
advantage of multi core node.  Apache give us the flexibility to run
multiple threads and multiple processes, and therefore much better
throughput. Though there are effects underway to make Keystone a
multi-worker process, those changes has not been landed and may
take time to mature.

3. SSL Authorization. Support for client certs.  Since SSL client
certificate already authenticate a given service, there's no need
for service to use a service token to validate user tokens. We simply
map the SSL client certificate attributes into Keystone identity attributes
to form a authorization context for API authorization.  Eventlet's SSL
capability is inferior to Apache by far! You can't get the
client SSL certificate attributes from eventlet.

Change-Id: I03a577b7e88c9026e6fc3cd6839b6c75e8072925
"}]
commit_message:
configure keystone with apache

Allow configuration of keystone with Apache via environement variable.
Below are the reasons why we need Apache:

1.  Keystone federation support requires Apache. Federation can only be
supported in conjunction with Apache as it needs both mod_mellon and mod_shib.

2. Performance. Unlike Nova or Swift, Keystone is using eventlet with a
single thread instead of multiple worker processes. So can't take
advantage of multi core node.  Apache give us the flexibility to run
multiple threads and multiple processes, and therefore much better
throughput. Though there are effects underway to make Keystone a
multi-worker process, those changes has not been landed and may
take time to mature.

3. SSL Authorization. Support for client certs.  Since SSL client
certificate already authenticate a given service, there's no need
for service to use a service token to validate user tokens. We simply
map the SSL client certificate attributes into Keystone identity attributes
to form a authorization context for API authorization.  Eventlet's SSL
capability is inferior to Apache by far! You can't get the
client SSL certificate attributes from eventlet.

Change-Id: I03a577b7e88c9026e6fc3cd6839b6c75e8072925

commit_message:
Refactors service url retrieval

This patch introduces functionality to set service URLs in the app.conf
file, either to:

- add service urls which aren't part of the serviceCatalog yet
- override service urls exposed through the serviceCatalog

Closes-Bug: 1586364

Change-Id: I730e3dea4f4b9f84d1974c7382f38ed70e57e315

>>> print 'help'

    print 'help'

commit_message:
Replace print statment with print function

In PY3, print should used as a function instead of a statement.
This is PY27 compatible as well.

For example, instances of the first case were replaced by the
second case:

>>> print 'help'
  File "<stdin>", line 1
    print 'help'
               ^
SyntaxError: Missing parentheses in call to 'print'

>>> print('help')
help

Partially implements: blueprint trove-python3
Change-Id: I21de65bc874d0fcfb51714857f8eaa97acb2f51d
Closes-bug: #1594741

commit_message:
Determine routing before delete on neutron events

Since delete notifications don't contain the parent network_id, we can't
determine a routing id in these cases. project_id would be an
alternative choice for routing but doesn't cover cases where subnets can
be attached to another tenant's network (and thus routing by project_id
would leave unpredictable results).

Patch runs a search request to get the parent (and routing) id for
subnet and port deletes. Upstream patch
https://review.openstack.org/#/c/289050 will make this unnecessary if it
ever merges; at that point we can get the network_id from the payload.

Additionally fixes some issues in the index helper code related to
accessing metafields (_routing, _parent) in searches that changed
between ES 1.x and 2.x.

Closes-Bug: #1588540
Change-Id: I6d6ccfe47d50a489d0c8e6eff8fbd7a792687b25

commit_message:
Moving to freezer-manage to create/update/delete mappings

Use freezer-manage instead of freezer-db-init to create/update/delete
elasticsearch mappings. freezer-manage will add couple of more
functionalities. freezer-manage reads from the same configuration
file like freezer-api and uses the same db info.

How to use:

To create the mappings::

freezer-manage db sync

To update the mappings::

freezer-manage db update

To remove the mappings::

freezer-manage db remove

To print the mappings::

freezer-manage db show

To update settings:

freezer-manage db update-settings

Change-Id: Ib1f8265b780c1e2300bcba45183309ea06c673d3
Implements: blueprint move-to-freezer-manage
Closes-Bug: #1587408

commit_message:
Remove remaining container_release properties

The lxc_container_create role has been updated to build containers to
the same distribution and release as the host machine. The
container_release property defined in environment files used to
generate inventory is no longer required.

I7d2aea8f6548feb381bf2354965f05fa0a9a99b8 removed this property from
half of the environment files. This change removes it from all remaining
files.

Change-Id: I8bff7613639676797159eac75cef0dd091bda7a4

commit_message:
Added qg-*, sg-* and vhu-* ports as default in included_interface_re.

By default router ports(qg-*), SG ports (sg-* VM SNAT traffic) and
VHU(vhost-user) ports for DPDK environment are enabled in
included_interface_re field in ovs.yaml.

Removed tap-* ports and qr-* ports to avoid data bloating.
If user still wants to configure the non default port they can
configure in ovs.yaml file and restart the monasca-gent to collect
the metrics.

Change-Id: I0984c8f1c2fb7d95fdb4da35bbc2214c51f82ba2

commit_message:
Improve partitions and disk metadata handling

Partitions schema and disk metadata at nodes must be updated only
if they are scheduled for reprovisioning, and the provisioning
method has changed to incompatible (i.e. from 'cobbler' to 'image')
due to the shift of release version.

Move logic that manages partitions from upgrade handlers to function
that actually initiates the re-provisioning of node. This ensures
that for every node this is applied only once and only if necessary.

Change-Id: I28718564543e3ccd92d985bd79c76e509e8eae1f
Closes-bug: 1585938
Closes-bug: 1575054

commit_message:
Move Resource exceptions to common module (1)

It is convenient to have all exceptions in exception module.
Also it is reduces namespace cluttering of resource module and decreases
the number of dependencies in other modules (we do not need to import resource
in some cases for now).
UpdateReplace exception is moved in this patch.

Change-Id: Ief441ca2022a0d50e88d709d1a062631479715b7

Currently, when a parameter is formatted wrong sphinx dies with a
cryptic error message:

    AttributeError: 'str' object has no attribute 'items'

This happens because the parameter is not recognized as dict.

This patch adds a check that ensures parameters are formatted correctly
by verifying that they're dicts.

Change-Id: I0140336cdcd9fd1d356d1fa50fd8dd15790ef8bd
"}]
commit_message:
Add warning for invalid parameters

Currently, when a parameter is formatted wrong sphinx dies with a
cryptic error message:

    AttributeError: 'str' object has no attribute 'items'

This happens because the parameter is not recognized as dict.

This patch adds a check that ensures parameters are formatted correctly
by verifying that they're dicts.

Change-Id: I0140336cdcd9fd1d356d1fa50fd8dd15790ef8bd

commit_message:
Use Zaqar signed URLs in software deployment

Zaqar queue, create a signature and use it as an authentication
mechanism.

commit_message:
Prevent unexpected exception if provision fail

Squashed commits from the 9.0:
- 79f99adf48de37d33b5e089472f91b2f7e614e55
  - fault tolerance for uploading errors
  - use upload file task instead of magnet directly
- e07e74eb5980421b47fbc64b6d6f50a955e7cad1
  - do not fail if no nodes were sent to reboot

Change-Id: I5b806f3d1411c4445a58b899b73eca035f5931b9

revisions:
[{'number': 4, 'created': '2016-05-26 14:12:29.000000000', 'files': ['deployment/puppet/osnailyfacter/templates/filter_rabbitmq_definitions.py', 'deployment/puppet/osnailyfacter/modular/astute/dump_rabbitmq_definitions.pp'], 'message': "Clean RabbitMQ definitions file

Added a script to clean up the rabbitmq definitions file which is
being generated during the post-deployment phase of a deployment.
Previosly the definitions file contained all RPC queues presented in
RabbitMQ after the successful deployment. These queues are one-off, and
their restoration via OCF-script leads to growth of unconsumed messages,
which, in turn, lead to RabbitMQ slowness and malfunctions.

This is a rework of the previously reverted change
Ie3f3194b3eaaa8dc28d1cd3442090b586e177306 which caused deployment
failures in some scenarios involving partial update. This happened
because the script was delivered in a separate package which has not
been updated during the partial update. Now the script is
delivered in the puppet's directory instead. Also introduced
additional regexp-matching logic to instantly remove all the RPC queues,
which were left in the previous version of the fix.

Change-Id: Ib2f8237692d7dab47b83ac886ff370686a5d22fe
Closes-Bug: #1497961
"}]
commit_message:
Clean RabbitMQ definitions file

Added a script to clean up the rabbitmq definitions file which is
being generated during the post-deployment phase of a deployment.
Previosly the definitions file contained all RPC queues presented in
RabbitMQ after the successful deployment. These queues are one-off, and
their restoration via OCF-script leads to growth of unconsumed messages,
which, in turn, lead to RabbitMQ slowness and malfunctions.

This is a rework of the previously reverted change
Ie3f3194b3eaaa8dc28d1cd3442090b586e177306 which caused deployment
failures in some scenarios involving partial update. This happened
because the script was delivered in a separate package which has not
been updated during the partial update. Now the script is
delivered in the puppet's directory instead. Also introduced
additional regexp-matching logic to instantly remove all the RPC queues,
which were left in the previous version of the fix.

Change-Id: Ib2f8237692d7dab47b83ac886ff370686a5d22fe
Closes-Bug: #1497961

ip_addresses list before pushing it to prevent having
duplicated ips when the ports status changes.

commit_message:
Insert 'rgw_frontends' parameter with default value into ceph.conf

In fuel-library, parameter 'rgw_frontends' was added to ceph.conf
file in version 8.0. This parameter always takes default value
and cannot be managed by deployment configuration engine (nailgun).

Add a line containing this parameter to the ceph.conf file while
moving it to upgraded controller. Set parameter to default value.

Change-Id: I19866f6e9c1b7590c017f471cb11e78c72102136
Closes-bug: 1575689
(cherry picked from commit 65e13c9a2a2edb015279f34d8965ee0c4a2d77d1)

commit_message:
Insert 'rgw_frontends' parameter with default value into ceph.conf

In fuel-library, parameter 'rgw_frontends' was added to ceph.conf
file in version 8.0. This parameter always takes default value
and cannot be managed by deployment configuration engine (nailgun).

Add a line containing this parameter to the ceph.conf file while
moving it to upgraded controller. Set parameter to default value.

Change-Id: I19866f6e9c1b7590c017f471cb11e78c72102136
Closes-bug: 1575689

commit_message:
Make dict.keys() PY3 compatible

The dict.keys()[0] will raise a TypeError in PY3, as dict.keys()
doesn't return a list any more in PY3 but a view of list.

commit_message:
Release repos list/update

Fuel releases contain metadata including default
set of rpm/deb repositories that are to be used
during cluster deployment. This change introduces
couple new subcommands that allow to view and change
the list of release repositories.

DocImpact
Change-Id: Ied9d69b98345318d7a92ca4c7093ac0424599cc3
Implements: blueprint fuelclient-modify-release-repos

Product id, enables to identify the capabilities of the device(ex, does the

Patch generalizes the _get_device_vendor function, enabling it to be used with
both block and net devices and add new function _get_device_vendor to get

Adds two attributes vendor_id, product_id to NetworkInterface class.

Closes-Bug: #1594196
Change-Id: Ifbbb4d630962ebc0b654b09cc074d0a3e4335074
Signed-off-by: yogananth subramanian <ysubrama@redhat.com>

commit_message:
Exporting Network Interface Product and Vendor ID to Inspector

Patch enables passing Product and Vendor ID to Inspector. These parameter
could be exposed using the Port's "extra" field.
Product id, enables to identify the capabilities of the device(ex, does the
device has SR-IOV capabilities or not), which would help in creating heat
template or building images using diskimage builder.

Patch generalizes the _get_device_vendor function, enabling it to be used with
both block and net devices and add new function _get_device_vendor to get
product id.
Adds two attributes vendor_id, product_id to NetworkInterface class.

Closes-Bug: #1594196
Change-Id: Ifbbb4d630962ebc0b654b09cc074d0a3e4335074
Signed-off-by: yogananth subramanian <ysubrama@redhat.com>

commit_message:
WADL to RST migration (part 1)

This brings the Images API Reference to the glance tree as part of
the effort described here:
https://wiki.openstack.org/wiki/Documentation/Migrate#API_Reference_Plan

This patch introduces (a) the tox environment to generate the api-ref,
and (b) the content of the Images v1 API reference converted to RST.
The content has been corrected where I noticed divergences with reality.

Note to reviewers: The conversion project is ongoing, that is, the doc
team is continuing to develop tools (for example, to display the response
codes in a table) and converging on a style for these docs.  So this isn't
a final product, there will be more patches later.  While this patch is
not perfect, it is pareto-optimal with respect to content (it's at least
as good as the current guide, and better in at least one place).  Thus
my advice, should you choose to take it, is that we should merge this
patch to get these docs in-tree, and make improvements as additional
patches that can focus on particular API calls rather than try to get
everything perfect on this patch.

Change-Id: I51dfaf1832108466f115ab183838c5f28e138312

commit_message:
Add configuration options for DISK_WAIT

https://review.openstack.org/#/c/320295/ introduced two internal
variables: _DISK_WAIT_ATTEMPTS and _DISK_WAIT_DELAY. These values are
hardcoded. This patch adds configuration options for these so
that an operator can change them based on their own needs/fleet of
hardware.

Change-Id: I2ba97669ec710fb4a435307466cd8add9c2293ba
Closes-Bug: #1585663

Service client modules in identity __init__

identity modules in v2 and v3, and define __all__, so that service

subject: Make `tempest init` working dir an abspath
revisions:
[{'number': 1, 'created': '2016-06-17 15:08:21.000000000', 'files': ['tempest/cmd/init.py'], 'message': 'Make `tempest init` working dir an abspath

The working directory can be either a relative path or absolute path
depending on how `tempest init` is called. If `tempest init` is called,
the working directory is absolute, but if `tempest init [dir]` is
called, the working directory is relative. The relative case leads to a
bug in setting up the tempest config file later.

We normalized and absolutized local_dir early on, and make everything
work with abspath. This minimize handling of the different paths and
reduces the chances of bugs from handling in later code.

Change-Id: I6dc314017eb264302ba68bbf25060e833d8e317a
Closes-Bug: #1593747
'}]
commit_message:
Make `tempest init` working dir an abspath

The working directory can be either a relative path or absolute path
depending on how `tempest init` is called. If `tempest init` is called,
the working directory is absolute, but if `tempest init [dir]` is
called, the working directory is relative. The relative case leads to a
bug in setting up the tempest config file later.

We normalized and absolutized local_dir early on, and make everything
work with abspath. This minimize handling of the different paths and
reduces the chances of bugs from handling in later code.

Change-Id: I6dc314017eb264302ba68bbf25060e833d8e317a
Closes-Bug: #1593747

[{'number': 1, 'created': '2016-05-31 15:40:11.000000000', 'files': ['oslo_config/cfg.py'], 'message': 'cfg: deprecate ListOpt

This patch deprecates ListOpt and mark it for removal. ListOpt is mostly used
for multi valued options. Unfortunately, it separate options using "," in their
definition string, which is less reliable than using MultiOpt which on the
opposite:

1. is more reliable by using a line for each value rather than spliting a
   string on ","
2. is easier to use as a CLI option (native  argparse support)

Change-Id: Iee64cb8919a1c29c18dcdc132d7d98d9c28c4421
'}]
commit_message:
cfg: deprecate ListOpt

This patch deprecates ListOpt and mark it for removal. ListOpt is mostly used
for multi valued options. Unfortunately, it separate options using "," in their
definition string, which is less reliable than using MultiOpt which on the
opposite:

1. is more reliable by using a line for each value rather than spliting a
   string on ","
2. is easier to use as a CLI option (native  argparse support)

This should improve the overall configuration user experience.

Closes-Bug: #1587315
Change-Id: Iee64cb8919a1c29c18dcdc132d7d98d9c28c4421

commit_message:
Disable rabbitmq cluster partition handling

Currently autoheal functionality is a subset of OCF script
functionality (autoheal is concerned only with network partitions, OCF
also handles all sort of cases where rabbitmq becomes stuck). But as
both of this functions cause stopping and starting of rabbits, it
results in unwanted interference - as we've observed in 1585128, where
it triggered bug in autoheal code.

Even if rabbitmq bug will be fixed, it makes no sense to use both
autoheal and OCF script (actually, when clustered rabbit will stop
getting stuck during network split, autoheal will be as good as OCF
script).

Change-Id: I38fbf6d50e9aed35f3c5e3bc1e17de7001304706
Closes-Bug: 1585128

commit_message:
Be consistent about context first argument in db api

By ensuring every db api function has the context as its first
argument, this raises the possiblity of using oslo.db recommended
session handling:
http://docs.openstack.org/developer/oslo.db/usage.html#session-handling

Change-Id: I3649bdbf254e2834e79984cc381a1db1ea9e78b8
Related-Bug: #1479723

commit_message:
use utf8 as default charset for all tables in mysql db

When we use "cinder-manager db sync" to create tables in mysql db,
some tables' charset is set to utf8 but some not. This will cause
db error when a foreign key is referenced to column in different
charset. This change set all tables in cinder use utf8 as default
charset.

Closes-bug: #1594195

Change-Id: I15a864dd1ad18aa1b3e3ff7fe511405d62a119cc

Do not print unhandled exception if in production

This change removes the printing of unhandled exceptions when not in
development mode. We should never return the unhandled exception
information when not in development mode.

commit_message:
Skip network allocation if 'none' is requested

If we're explicitly told to not allocate networks, then
don't, skip network allocation.

This also skips network deallocation if we can tell that
we wouldn't have allocated networks because 'none' was
requested for networking. Note, however, that this is just
an optimization when requested_networks is available - which
is not the case with a local delete from the compute API.
Even if we didn't check in the deallocate case it would be fine
since deallocate_for_instance in nova-network and neutron
network APIs won't find any resources to delete since none
were allocated to begin with. But at least we can try to save
ourselves some RPC/DB (nova-network) and REST API (neutron)
traffic.

Part of blueprint get-me-a-network

Change-Id: Ia0d5189453df825805dab028cc81de7dfa0d6c84

commit_message:
processutils: add support for missing process limits

The original commit adding support for process limits only wired
up address space, max files and resident set size limits. This
is not sufficient to enable nova to protect qemu-img commands
against malicious images.

This commit adds support for the remaining limits supported
by python: core file size, cpu time, data size, file size,
locked memory size, max processes and stack size.

Related-bug: #1449062
Change-Id: I164c4b35e1357a0f80ed7fe00a7ae8f49df92e31
(cherry picked from commit 8af826953d1ad2cab2ecf360e0c794de70a367c3)
(cherry picked from commit 5f417f8e9656e097070036daced26d8b0f3728c3)

commit_message:
Make registering error handlers compliant with Flask 0.11

With Flask 0.11 setting error handlers by directly modifying
app.error_handler_spec dictionary leads to AttributeErrors.
It should be done by using register_error_handler method or
errorhandler decorator.

Change-Id: I2f41ab2b9ea8c4a964b16acdf77def1b08b64a6e
Closes-Bug: #1587849
(cherry picked from commit 685f7c17fd5c882e1b7198507112c2ebb8fce745)

commit_message:
Add support to the history import tools for release-type

When trying to use the history import tools we need to use the correct
release-type setting to validate tags.

We can't use versionutils.validate_version() as it's a generator which is
hard to use in a sorted() function.  Insetad introduce
versionutils.canonical_version() which will return the version is valid
or raise a ValueError() exception.

Change-Id: If10aab4c573342227e2909fd84f843c96f3abc43

commit_message:
Add Support for validating 4 digit verion strings

The xstatic packages have a 4 digit verion number 3-digit semver as
supplied by upstream and a local build number.  PBR only supports 3
digit semver.

To work with that create the concpet of a release type that can have
slightly different validation rules.  In this case use the 'packaging'
library.

This will allow the horizon team to use the standard release process.

For refernce see:
https://blueprints.launchpad.net/horizon/+spec/xstatic-release-process

Change-Id: Ie0f33097c31ee4006ec58147b35731913f7b6f4b

commit_message:
Tests: Use mock for notifier tests

Rather than having a fake_notifier which stores notifications,
just mock notify calls and ensure that the expected calls
are made.

The previous method of doing this was fundamentally flawed
and racy -- this should fix up the reoccuring issues with
notifications tests failures.

Closes-Bug: #1582306

Change-Id: Ied505362889d402a296fdfd65db758668f2a4d65

commit_message:
Repair fuelweb_admin network metadata

When upgrade from version 6.0 to 8.0, the fuelweb_admin network metadata
is restored from version 6.0. However, since version 6.1, certain params
in the metadata changed, which is reflected in fixture/admin_network.json
file.

Set 'gateway' field for network group 'fuelweb_admin' to the address
of the Fuel Master node.

Set 'vip_type' field in ip_addrs table for the 'fuelweb_admin' to NULL.

Change-Id: Ice94dcb7826b5357b9aaab56ea1632d77160db5e
Partial-bug: 1573075

revisions:
[{'number': 1, 'created': '2016-06-14 13:08:20.000000000', 'files': ['reference/projects.yaml', 'reference/retired-projects.yaml'], 'message': 'Remove Packaging-Deb project team

The Packaging-Deb team was added August 13, 2015. Since that date
we added a requirement for minimum activity (following the rejection
of the Kosmos team), so it seems fair (after a decent grace period)
to revisit previously-approved official project teams based on that
new requirement.

The Packaging-Deb team specifies 25 repositories, of which only
one was created. That repository has two boilerplate commits[1].
Progress is not being discussed on the ML or in regular IRC
meetings. As far as OpenStack is concerned, this team basically
hasn't started yet.

When the issue was raised at the last PTL elections, Thomas Goirand
(the original team creator and main contributor) justified the
team existence in a ML thread[2]. In particular, the team is
actually active, but on alioth.debian.org git repositories.

While the team may be active, it is not an OpenStack project team,
it is a Debian project team, and all the visible work currently
happens there (on Debian git repositories and IRC channels). So I
don't think that should count toward "activity" for the OpenStack
official project team we are considering.

Thomas also said that progress is being stalled on getting a Debian
image supported in OpenStack Infrastructure, an objective that has
been lacking the necessary manpower or priority to be completed
until now. Being punted back to unofficial status would undo the
last 10 months efforts.

While this might have been true one year ago, we now no longer
undo anything when a project team is made unofficial, the git
repositories can stay up under the same name, and infrastructure
bits can be configured the same. So making the unborn project
"unofficial" does not undo any work that's been done, it only
reflects the actual status of the project team.

When the team starts working on the OpenStack side and the
repositories see some activity, I'll be more than happy to
reconsider adding this team. But for the time being we need
to remove it, if only to be fair with other nascent new teams
that we reject based on lack of past activity.

[1] https://git.openstack.org/cgit/openstack/deb-openstack-pkg-tools/log/
[2] http://lists.openstack.org/pipermail/openstack-dev/2016-March/089369.html

Change-Id: If51c21cfc1e918a18921b5399b55e7805a1f9eea
'}]
commit_message:
Remove Packaging-Deb project team

The Packaging-Deb team was added August 13, 2015. Since that date
we added a requirement for minimum activity (following the rejection
of the Kosmos team), so it seems fair (after a decent grace period)
to revisit previously-approved official project teams based on that
new requirement.

The Packaging-Deb team specifies 25 repositories, of which only
one was created. That repository has two boilerplate commits[1].
Progress is not being discussed on the ML or in regular IRC
meetings. As far as OpenStack is concerned, this team basically
hasn't started yet.

When the issue was raised at the last PTL elections, Thomas Goirand
(the original team creator and main contributor) justified the
team existence in a ML thread[2]. In particular, the team is
actually active, but on alioth.debian.org git repositories.

While the team may be active, it is not an OpenStack project team,
it is a Debian project team, and all the visible work currently
happens there (on Debian git repositories and IRC channels). So I
don't think that should count toward "activity" for the OpenStack
official project team we are considering.

Thomas also said that progress is being stalled on getting a Debian
image supported in OpenStack Infrastructure, an objective that has
been lacking the necessary manpower or priority to be completed
until now. Being punted back to unofficial status would undo the
last 10 months efforts.

While this might have been true one year ago, we now no longer
undo anything when a project team is made unofficial, the git
repositories can stay up under the same name, and infrastructure
bits can be configured the same. So making the unborn project
"unofficial" does not undo any work that's been done, it only
reflects the actual status of the project team.

When the team starts working on the OpenStack side and the
repositories see some activity, I'll be more than happy to
reconsider adding this team. But for the time being we need
to remove it, if only to be fair with other nascent new teams
that we reject based on lack of past activity.

[1] https://git.openstack.org/cgit/openstack/deb-openstack-pkg-tools/log/
[2] http://lists.openstack.org/pipermail/openstack-dev/2016-March/089369.html

Change-Id: If51c21cfc1e918a18921b5399b55e7805a1f9eea

commit_message:
Update default network settings only for available releases

After upgrade it's possible to manage older releases but not to deploy fresh
clusters. Since there is no TUN segmentation type in older releases we can
get KeyError.

Change-Id: I9b22f7fc9b4eac8f1418cd6da81b39df9efaa86f

Update default network settings only for available releases

After upgrade it's possible to manage older releases but not to deploy fresh
clusters. Since there is no TUN segmentation type in older releases we can
get KeyError.

clusters. Since there is no TUN segmentation type in older releases we can
get KeyError.

commit_message:
Validate nodes roles to exclude upgrade of single controller

The proper sequence to upgrade controllers is:

- upgrade primary controller in isolation
- cut over to the new control plane
- upgrade remaining controllers at once

To exclude the possibility to upgrade single controller after
the cutover, add validation of roles of nodes to upgrade and
stop if the only node passed to the script is a CIC.

Change-Id: Ie91ae35acb7e36103004a59c92cb495837e0dca0
Closes-bug: 1584656

subject: Remove oslo_utils.timeutils.total_seconds() usage + catch DriverLoadFailure for get_transport optional + fix CI failure due to oslo.messaging 5.0.0 + correct concurrency of gabbi
revisions:

This function was deprecated and has been removed.

+

new oslo.messaging 5.2.0 release will raise
oslo_messaging.transport.DriverLoadFailure if no existent transport
driver, hence breaks our code and unit test as well.

This patch fixes it by adding DriverLoadFailure to catch list.

Closes-Bug: #1588151
(cherry picked from commit d7f8ce94e433da8af3660ecf52715a04c221fde5)

Recently, oslo.messaging does a refactor [1] which causes
get_batch_notification_listener returns a new type
BatchNotificationServer instead of previous MessageHandlingServer,
they have different attributes, so our test code which relies on

commit_message:
Remove oslo_utils.timeutils.total_seconds() usage + catch DriverLoadFailure for get_transport optional + fix CI failure due to oslo.messaging 5.0.0 + correct concurrency of gabbi

This function was deprecated and has been removed.

+

new oslo.messaging 5.2.0 release will raise
oslo_messaging.transport.DriverLoadFailure if no existent transport
driver, hence breaks our code and unit test as well.

This patch fixes it by adding DriverLoadFailure to catch list.

Closes-Bug: #1588151
(cherry picked from commit d7f8ce94e433da8af3660ecf52715a04c221fde5)

+

Recently, oslo.messaging does a refactor [1] which causes
get_batch_notification_listener returns a new type
BatchNotificationServer instead of previous MessageHandlingServer,
they have different attributes, so our test code which relies on
MessageHandlingServer fails in CI gate.

This patch makes test code not rely on oslo.messaging details.

[1] https://github.com/openstack/oslo.messaging/commit/990d894eaf0d18941b56d89bff2bca51de375640

(cherry picked from commit 23d5c9f648d8352aa205fbe46ba9796a5424874f)

+

Correct concurrency of gabbi tests for gabbi 1.22.0

When running gabbi under testr, concurrency grouping is controlled
by a regex in .testr.conf. A module name change in gabbi 1.22.0
inadvertently broke the grouping. This change should work for
old and new versions.

(cherry picked from commit 8fcbc8de4ea878bdec1ef8754eaf965e176854b3)

Change-Id: I02b5d1b3f4a9169cbf428a5eff9c6705494741af

commit_message:
[contributor] Update guideline of RST reference

Sphinx allows separate reference definition, but it is not translator
friendly because translators cannot control links (for example,
they may want to use links to translated documents), so we recommend
not to use separate reference definitions.

This convention is already applied in reviews but not documented so far.

References:
ML discussion: http://lists.openstack.org/pipermail/openstack-docs/2015-November/007955.html
Networking guide changes: https://review.openstack.org/#/c/301265/

commit_message:
Update l2/port.pp vlan interface name regexp.

Previously only interfaces with aaaNNN.XXX were recognized as vlan
subinterfaces where NNN and XXX are digits and NNN is required.
It doesn't allow to create vlan subinterfaces with names like
aaa-bbb.XXX.
This patch updates regexp to recognize names like:
aaaNNN.XXX aaa-bbb.XXX aaa.XXX aaa-bbb-NNN.XXX

Closes-Bug: #1593142
Change-Id: Ic3d97cf5f32cb1107c185fc9ce6c980303e0fc92

jenkins/jobs/projects.yaml.

commit_message:
Merge gerrit jobs for project-config

Both gate-project-config-projects-yaml and gate-project-config-gerrit
test files in gerrit directory, both check ACLs a swell. Let's merge
those into one job since in most cases both need to be run anyway and
the name projects-yaml might be confused with
jenkins/jobs/projects.yaml.

Note that this one leaves the projects tox environment in so that
testing of this change passes.

Change-Id: I34324643c26d0bcf2d24ce1dc51250ad53f2d48f

commit_message:
Start and Stop DatasourceDriver in new architecture

PollingDatasourceDriver starts polling once the driver has been
initialized and will never stop polling. This patch enables
PollingDatasourceDriver to start polling after its start() is
called and to stop polling after its stop() is called.

Change-Id: I395e5ddbfa6907cc26d4636eeb1ecbb954baae8d

commit_message:
Add helper functions for work with temp dirs and files

* Add function get_tempname required for create temporary filename
It has optional arguments: dir and prefix:
dir setup a directory where this file will be created
prefix setup a prefix value of the file

Usage:

    from octane.util import tempfile

    tmp_name = tempfile.get_tempname()

* Adding of contextmanager temp_dir is required for creating of tempdir
before code block and removing it upon completion of the block.

Usage:

    from octane.util import tempfile

    with tempfile.temp_dir() as my_tmp_dir:
        # code block
        ...

Change-Id: I20b8a0109a85ef41708fa8c9e7e050b391ed039e
(cherry picked from commit a15d657e65bfde9211794d96df6d7c3fb2baa4ef)

commit_message:
Add helper functions for work with temp dirs and files

* Add function get_tempname required for create temporary filename
It has optional arguments: dir and prefix:
dir setup a directory where this file will be created
prefix setup a prefix value of the file

Usage:

    from octane.util import tempfile

    tmp_name = tempfile.get_tempname()

* Adding of contextmanager temp_dir is required for creating of tempdir
before code block and removing it upon completion of the block.

Usage:

commit_message:
Add KMIP Experiment Check to Barbican

Barbican currently supports a plugin architecture for secret stores.
One such secret store implementation is the KMIP secret store. There
are no checks in place at the moment to test the functionality of
Barbican with this plugin.

This patch creates a new Jenkins job to test Barbican with the KMIP
secret store plugin. The end effect will be running all of Barbican's
functional tests using a KMIP secret store plugin. This change enables
the PyKMIP server to run as part of the devstack setup.

The tests can only be run on the latest code. The older stable
branches for kilo, liberty, and mitaka are not supported because the
necessary devstack plugin code is not backported to those branches.
The KMIP secret store job is experimental for now until tests verify
the correct operation.

Change-Id: I3fc6abe6f34bcb31c9ea01bfd7c7ccfd22b28bcc
Depends-On: Ib804fa97545f14ed866bfd73bb251e85923a2e4e

commit_message:
Add new project: networking-icc

This project implements an API extension to Neutron in order to
enable L2/L3 connectivity between multiple overlay networks located
in multiple OpenStack clouds. This project re-uses Dragonflow
code base with its SDN controller, run-time database and pub/sub
architecture to provide inter-cloud connection between multiple
ICC (Inter-Cloud Connector) devices. The project in meant to work
with hardware and software (e.g. OVS) forwarders alike.

This project is meant to be used by Tricircle project (Top
OpenStack) providing it a way to connect multiple Botom OpenStacks.

Change-Id: I4c250d3dec79d89a78b823f4c151c0029144273a

commit_message:
Start using pre-prov creds in dsvm-layer4

Since pre-provisioned credentials in Tempest are now stable,
I'd like to use that in the gate, along with dynamic credentials,
to ensure both mechanisms are preserved intact.

Starting with layer4 job that runs against tempest only util we
have further proven reliability.

Depends-on: I9db0154a364cec3214b5cabd8a7766a110c2b973

commit_message:
Check immutable and update_allowed conflict in schema validation

This doesn't check any user input, but checks the validity of the
schema itself, so better to do it during schema validation.
Note, that now heat engine doesn't start in the case of invalid schema.

of services and the searched service is not among the first
'list_limit' services. The API should first filter by name and
only afterwards truncate the result list.

Also, this patch fixes setting the 'truncated' attribute of the
driver's hint.limit object when truncating the list outside of
driver_hints.truncated decorator, problem exposed by fixing the

Change-Id: I832f542c3cb0faf94a1e5bce5a894f7f4d26a8de
"}]
commit_message:
/services?name=<name> API fails when using list_limit

When using list_limit configuration option in Default section of
keystone.conf, the /services?name=<service_name> API fails to find
the service if list_limit value is smaller than the total number
of services and the searched service is not among the first
'list_limit' services. The API should first filter by name and
only afterwards truncate the result list.

Also, this patch fixes setting the 'truncated' attribute of the
driver's hint.limit object when truncating the list outside of
driver_hints.truncated decorator, problem exposed by fixing the
problem described in the first paragraph.

Closes-Bug: #1594482
Change-Id: I832f542c3cb0faf94a1e5bce5a894f7f4d26a8de

subject: Treat empty windows as OK for deterministic alarms
revisions:
[{'number': 1, 'created': '2016-06-20 18:36:57.000000000', 'files': ['thresh/src/main/java/monasca/thresh/domain/model/SubAlarmStats.java', 'thresh/src/test/java/monasca/thresh/infrastructure/thresholding/MetricAggregationBoltTest.java'], 'message': 'Treat empty windows as OK for deterministic alarms

Using the standard case of count(log_message) > 1, getting no
log_message measurements should be treated as OK. However, the old code
uses the emptyWindowObservationThreshold for both deterministic and
non-deterministic alarms which means that there must be 3 empty windows
before the deterministic alarm transitions to OK.

This change cause the evaluation of the Alarm to treat an empty window
as OK for deterministic alarms. So, count(log_message) > 1, getting no
measurements in a window will transition the alarm back to OK

Change-Id: I19a04bf78f907b23ef583409f2def54771c07d72
'}]
commit_message:
Treat empty windows as OK for deterministic alarms

Using the standard case of count(log_message) > 1, getting no
log_message measurements should be treated as OK. However, the old code
uses the emptyWindowObservationThreshold for both deterministic and
non-deterministic alarms which means that there must be 3 empty windows
before the deterministic alarm transitions to OK.

This change cause the evaluation of the Alarm to treat an empty window
as OK for deterministic alarms. So, count(log_message) > 1, getting no
measurements in a window will transition the alarm back to OK

Change-Id: I19a04bf78f907b23ef583409f2def54771c07d72

commit_message:
Support ML2 option to enable security groups

Add support for the ML2 enable_security_group option under [securitygroup]
in ml2_conf.ini. This option is set to True by default and will control
whether or not ACLs are applied to ports and the port binding value for
CAP_PORT_FILTER.

Also, update devstack plugin to set enable_security_group based on
Q_USE_SECGROUP and comment out firewall_driver since it isn't used by OVN.

And finally, add the security group options to the neutron-ovn-db-sync-util
command.

Change-Id: I73ca9a34ea34f781cbec5680b44e98da309365bb
Closes-Bug: #1588935

commit_message:
delete stale ovsdb table entries from mysql db

whenever l2gateway_agnet.ini is reconfigured to the same ovsdb identifier
but different IP, then we need to clean the mysql db entries from earlier
configured ovsdb_identifier and IP.

For Ex: l2gateway_agent is connected to "ovsdb1:10.10.10.10:6632",
but when you change l2gateway_agent.ini to "ovsdb1:20.20.20.20:6632",
then the mysql entries related to "ovsdb1:10.10.10.10:6632" should be cleaned.

Change-Id: I72cd5a5e2ea27c2a6b37865c3517e614f901aecf
Closes-Bug:1588809

commit_message:
Use is_valid_ipv4 from oslo.utils

In module netaddr valid_ipv4 raise exception AddrFormatError
if address is specified as empty string. Method is_valid_ipv4
catches the exception and returns boolean value. So we'd better
use it from oslo.utils.

Change-Id: Ic54f2081575fa256e387e3d4bfb718895b580766

commit_message:
Merge tag '6.1.0'

This is a null-merge of the 6.1.0 release tag back into the master
branch so that the 6.1.0 tag will appear in the git commit history of
the master branch. It contains no actual changes to the master branch,
regardless of how our code review system's UI represents it. Please
ask in #openstack-infra if you have any questions, and otherwise try
to merge this as quickly as possible to avoid later conflicts on the
master branch.

Change-Id: I94019769a3ebcaba66e8bc1544a3563f325c1735

commit_message:
approved spec directory

Create approved spec directory for store all specs that been approved in this
release but not been implemented yet.
Through this way, it's no longer required to seperate implemented specs or
non-implemented specs in each release directory. Also possible for
blueprints to plan cross releases.

Change-Id: Iee23d66abcceebfed5fe97b04163de446193ee1d

commit_message:
Create resources for environment

Consider that user may have different environment setting under different
scope. We should create resources for environment, give user ability to
dynamically set (or registry) environment parameters, resource_registry,
or other section in environment file.

blueprint environment-resource

Change-Id: I483fdce00594da631dd40708446b223f45822e17

commit_message:
add l3 cache usage meter

Some Intel processor families (e.g. the Intel Xeon processor E5 v3
family) introduced CMT (Cache Monitoring Technology) to measure the
usage of l3 cache (last level cache) by applications running on the
platform. This spec introduces one new meter to get l3 cache usage
statistics based on Intel CMT feature.

Implements: blueprint l3-cache-meter
Change-Id: I7f38e80776e1e55533b33e9c72dcab6d3c12abb4

commit_message:
Modals should inherit from the theme

* Fullscreen Modals have been removed
  These weren't working properly anyways, and the styling is very
  unpleasant: https://i.imgur.com/QfvGli7.png

* Added two more modal sizes: xs and xl, and added all modals sizes
  to the theme preview page.  Also updated the theme preview page
  to use fa-close instead of 'x'.

* Cleaned up Spinner css to use modal sizes properly.  Themability
  of spinner to come later.

* Confirmation Modal JavaScript was cleaned up, and contents turned
  into an easier to digest client side template. Themability of
  client side templates show cased in 'material' design.

* 'material' confirmation dialog was altered to show how themes can
  make use of overriding client-side templates.

* Moved the Bootstrap helper variables into its own file.

* Added helper variables for various modal calculations.

Change-Id: I599ad2ffcf3034a24a19bc87e6ebed3eab079f45

commit_message:
Mask password on agent lookup according to policy

We currently mask passwords in driver_info for all API responses,
except for agent lookups. This is because driver_vendor_passthru
just expects a dict to return as JSON in the response, and doesn't
modify it at all.

Change lookup to follow the defined policy when returning the node
object in the response, the same way we do for other API responses.

Co-authored-by: Jim Rollenhagen <jim@jimrollenhagen.com>

Change-Id: Ib19d2f86d3527333e905fdbf1f09fc3dc8b8c5a7
Closes-Bug: #1572796
(cherry picked from commit 426a306fb580762e97ada04e1253dedd9b64d410)

commit_message:
Added heat.resource_type custom constraint

This constraint will validate that a parameter value is a valid resource
type within the context of the template (that is, taking into account
the environment file(s) passed in as well).

Change-Id: I82b18d52982c2731370df9ea4ea0e398bf7702f2
Closes-Bug: #1545857

commit_message:
Remove duplicate unit test resource tracker

Removes the test class that tested the "periodic update resource"
functionality in test_resource_tracker.py. This wasn't testing any code
paths that were not already being tested by test_tracker.py's
TestUpdateComputeNode and TestUpdateAvailableResource test case classes.

commit_message:
add FIXME tag for extra argument 'topic' in scheduler rpc api

Some functions in scheduler rpc api receive unused argument
'topic'. We can't fix it now as we may interact with old services.
It can only be fixed when we do a major version bump and drop the
old compatibility. Now we add two FIXME tags in case we forget it
one day.

Change-Id: Iafd60bb51a2d7c8eab909d35f4b4de120a1172bb
Partial-Bug: #1593149

subject: provide a replacement for the deprecated isotime()
revisions:
[{'number': 3, 'created': '2016-06-17 11:51:02.000000000', 'files': ['oslo_utils/timeutils.py', 'oslo_utils/tests/test_timeutils.py'], 'message': 'provide a replacement for the deprecated isotime()

This change proposes a new timeutils.isoformat() to replace the earlier
one which was deprecated.

Several issues with the old isotime() function became apparent in
reviewing the steps required to handle the deprecation of
isotime(). These are detailed in the bug 1592181.

I strongly urge all reviewers to read the bug (referenced) and the
comments as part of the review.

WARNING: This code as proposed could introduce inconsistencies in the
way in which the earlier isotime() returns results. Specifically,
these two situations are known.

1. If you provide a timestamp that includes timezone information, the
old isotime() would wilfully ignore it, the new isoformat() function
will produce offset information in the resulting string. If the
timezone is UTC, you will get the 'Z' suffix, if it is non-UTC, you
will get the full 6 character offset +/-hh:mm.

2. If you provided isotime() with the subsecond parameter it returned
the (im)PERFECT_TIMESTAMP_FORMAT which included subsecond information
but NO timezone information. The new isoformat() returns timezone
information. If the timezone is UTC, you will get the 'Z' suffix, if
it is non-UTC, you will get the full 6 character offset +/-hh:mm.

In addition, a behavior which makes this implementation of isoformat()
differ from the original is that if you provide isoformat() with a
timestamp that includes invalid timezone information (such as an
offset greater than one day) then isoformat() will throw a
ValueError. The old isotime() was wilfully unaware and you wouldn't
get such an exception.

Tests have been proposed which exercise the new isoformat() function.

The term "wilfully unaware" that I use in the description above is
non-standard. It is not the same as 'naive'. Rather, 'wilfully
unaware' indicates code that knowingly treats timestamps as naive
without checking or making any consideration for whether they are
aware or naive.

I believe that this code, warts and all is better than having multiple
buggy copies of isotime() in each project; each just slightly
different from the other to make your skin crawl. It is generally
advisable when you have bad apples, to put them all together and away
from the good ones. This change attempts to do that.

Change-Id: Ifb367a1f96a663a1d54b1770b9d20bbffdba491c
Related: Ic5abf6669edd4f1a9fd62e61f437565aa887aebe
Closes-Bug: #1592181
'}]
commit_message:
provide a replacement for the deprecated isotime()

This change proposes a new timeutils.isoformat() to replace the earlier
one which was deprecated.

Several issues with the old isotime() function became apparent in
reviewing the steps required to handle the deprecation of
isotime(). These are detailed in the bug 1592181.

I strongly urge all reviewers to read the bug (referenced) and the
comments as part of the review.

WARNING: This code as proposed could introduce inconsistencies in the
way in which the earlier isotime() returns results. Specifically,
these two situations are known.

1. If you provide a timestamp that includes timezone information, the
old isotime() would wilfully ignore it, the new isoformat() function
will produce offset information in the resulting string. If the
timezone is UTC, you will get the 'Z' suffix, if it is non-UTC, you
will get the full 6 character offset +/-hh:mm.

2. If you provided isotime() with the subsecond parameter it returned
the (im)PERFECT_TIMESTAMP_FORMAT which included subsecond information
but NO timezone information. The new isoformat() returns timezone
information. If the timezone is UTC, you will get the 'Z' suffix, if
it is non-UTC, you will get the full 6 character offset +/-hh:mm.

In addition, a behavior which makes this implementation of isoformat()
differ from the original is that if you provide isoformat() with a
timestamp that includes invalid timezone information (such as an
offset greater than one day) then isoformat() will throw a
ValueError. The old isotime() was wilfully unaware and you wouldn't
get such an exception.

Tests have been proposed which exercise the new isoformat() function.

The term "wilfully unaware" that I use in the description above is
non-standard. It is not the same as 'naive'. Rather, 'wilfully
unaware' indicates code that knowingly treats timestamps as naive
without checking or making any consideration for whether they are
aware or naive.

I believe that this code, warts and all is better than having multiple
buggy copies of isotime() in each project; each just slightly
different from the other to make your skin crawl. It is generally
advisable when you have bad apples, to put them all together and away
from the good ones. This change attempts to do that.

Change-Id: Ifb367a1f96a663a1d54b1770b9d20bbffdba491c
Related: Ic5abf6669edd4f1a9fd62e61f437565aa887aebe
Closes-Bug: #1592181

commit_message:
Remove useless str()

This change uses:

  LOG.exception(_LE("... %s"), cmd)

instead of:

  LOG.exception(_LE("... %s"), str(cmd))

because %s converts python object using str.

Change-Id: I19c21f6e357f3cba3f5937f63a690628205d5e5b

subject: Fix unwanted unmounting of /usr/share/oem
revisions:
[{'number': 2, 'created': '2016-06-21 20:59:13.000000000', 'files': ['imagebuild/coreos/oem/cloud-config.yml'], 'message': 'Fix unwanted unmounting of /usr/share/oem

Creating specific partitions will cause a udev event to trigger,
causing systemd to attempt to mount the new partition at /usr/share/oem.

This mount will not succeed, but will unmount /usr/share/oem,
causing ironic-python-agent to die.

Masking this unit disables this behavior.

Change-Id: Ifea3482f36a354cbf988e6f6003f4284c5c2a21d
Closes-bug: #1592163
(cherry picked from commit da0a8aff88e67fce7603b03a220b77b451349e7d)
'}]
commit_message:
Fix unwanted unmounting of /usr/share/oem

Creating specific partitions will cause a udev event to trigger,
causing systemd to attempt to mount the new partition at /usr/share/oem.

This mount will not succeed, but will unmount /usr/share/oem,
causing ironic-python-agent to die.

Masking this unit disables this behavior.

Change-Id: Ifea3482f36a354cbf988e6f6003f4284c5c2a21d
Closes-bug: #1592163
(cherry picked from commit da0a8aff88e67fce7603b03a220b77b451349e7d)

commit_message:
Support systemd on Fedora-based distros

Modify start_ceph and stop_ceph functions to use 'systemctl'
and ceph.target for Fedora and RHEL7 deployments with Infernalis
or later as specified in ceph release notes [1].

Also note that non-ubuntu systems may install from gitbuilder.

[1] http://docs.ceph.com/docs/master/release-notes/#upgrading-from-hammer

Change-Id: I45a1853d6c2dea11e83134c3134a890aed30a9cc

subject: Fix unwanted unmounting of /usr/share/oem
revisions:
[{'number': 1, 'created': '2016-06-21 20:51:57.000000000', 'files': ['imagebuild/coreos/oem/cloud-config.yml'], 'message': 'Fix unwanted unmounting of /usr/share/oem

Creating specific partitions will cause a udev event to trigger,
causing systemd to attempt to mount the new partition at /usr/share/oem.

This mount will not succeed, but will unmount /usr/share/oem,
causing ironic-python-agent to die.

Masking this unit disables this behavior.

Change-Id: Ifea3482f36a354cbf988e6f6003f4284c5c2a21d
Closes-bug: #1592163
(cherry picked from commit da0a8aff88e67fce7603b03a220b77b451349e7d)
'}]
commit_message:
Fix unwanted unmounting of /usr/share/oem

Creating specific partitions will cause a udev event to trigger,
causing systemd to attempt to mount the new partition at /usr/share/oem.

This mount will not succeed, but will unmount /usr/share/oem,
causing ironic-python-agent to die.

Masking this unit disables this behavior.

Change-Id: Ifea3482f36a354cbf988e6f6003f4284c5c2a21d
Closes-bug: #1592163
(cherry picked from commit da0a8aff88e67fce7603b03a220b77b451349e7d)

subject: Fix an issue with oslo_config_project paste config
revisions:
[{'number': 1, 'created': '2016-06-21 20:02:43.000000000', 'files': ['keystonemiddleware/_common/config.py'], 'message': 'Fix an issue with oslo_config_project paste config

When oslo_config_project is specified in the paste config, we need to
lookup the configuration file properly. Commit
f8c150a9cc9b407b2df87244daf3342177260e90 changed the way we looked up
for the default config files, and passed an empty list instead of None,
which means that no look were done anymore. This restores the previous
behavior.

Change-Id: I6aec548cec24dfcd48e4c116c07f53cc097c6059
Closes-Bug: #1594930
'}]
commit_message:
Fix an issue with oslo_config_project paste config

When oslo_config_project is specified in the paste config, we need to
lookup the configuration file properly. Commit
f8c150a9cc9b407b2df87244daf3342177260e90 changed the way we looked up
for the default config files, and passed an empty list instead of None,
which means that no look were done anymore. This restores the previous
behavior.

Change-Id: I6aec548cec24dfcd48e4c116c07f53cc097c6059
Closes-Bug: #1594930

revisions:
